snippet: News that House Republicans agreed to a three-month extension of the debt ceiling helped, as did reports that China’s growth was not quite as slow as believed.
abstract: Dow Jones industrial average and Standard & Poor's 500-stock index close at five-year highs as market has its third consecutive week of gains after solid start to quarterly earnings season.
lead_paragraph: News that House Republicans agreed to a three-month extension of the debt ceiling helped, as did reports that China’s growth was not quite as slow as believed.

headline.seo: Wall Street at 5-Year High, Lifted by Strong Corporate Earnings
headline.main: Earnings Vigor Drives Another Week of Gains
headline.print_headline: Earnings Vigor Drives Another Week of Gains
